1
00:00:04,250 --> 00:00:13,540


2
00:01:32,459 --> 00:01:34,921
   

3
00:01:34,921 --> 00:01:37,128
   

4
00:01:37,128 --> 00:01:39,994
   

5
00:01:45,959 --> 00:01:48,340
Yan, have a date cake. Okay?

6
00:01:56,632 --> 00:01:58,185
What are you looking at?

7
00:01:58,185 --> 00:02:01,120
About last time, is there no follow-up?

8
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,439
What "last time"?

9
00:02:02,439 --> 00:02:03,719
I told you.

10
00:02:03,719 --> 00:02:07,100
The girl was extremely drunk, so it wasn't for real.

11
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:09,280
- Miao, have a bun, okay? 
 - Yes, eat the bun.

12
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:11,765
I warned you long ago, but you wouldn't listen and went looking for her.

13
00:02:11,765 --> 00:02:14,034
Now look. You got dumped again.

14
00:02:14,034 --> 00:02:15,319
Girl.

15
00:02:15,319 --> 00:02:17,574
That's in the past. Why bring it up?

16
00:02:17,574 --> 00:02:19,480
I'm obliged to because that woman is crazy.

17
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,000
Why can't I mention it?

18
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,444
Brother, I'm begging you to stop looking for her.

19
00:02:24,444 --> 00:02:26,280
What's so great about her?

20
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:29,080
She's the most obnoxious and cold-hearted person I've ever met.

21
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,479
Heartless.

22
00:02:30,479 --> 00:02:31,800
Be quiet.

23
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,439
Miao Miao.

24
00:02:33,439 --> 00:02:34,939
That's enough.

25
00:02:35,919 --> 00:02:38,440
Why are you so against her?

26
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,439
She isn't like what you said.

27
00:02:40,439 --> 00:02:42,039
Yeah, right.

28
00:02:46,639 --> 00:02:49,860
She's the most fragile and timid person I know.

29
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:51,520
That woman?

30
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:54,939
She wishes to go wild, let loose, and be free.

31
00:02:54,939 --> 00:02:56,960
She doesn't want to submit.

32
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:01,381
She pretends to be strong, but in fact, her innermost being is weak.

33
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:07,286
A character like hers is the most useless.

34
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,879
Seems like it's most useful to you.

35
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:11,779
She has you wrapped around her little finger.

36
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:17,759
I don't know if there's any use.

37
00:03:17,759 --> 00:03:22,035
Either way, I just don't think she's right for you.

38
00:03:22,035 --> 00:03:24,759
Oh right, I remember that Li Meng from the detachment.

39
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:26,840
I think that lady is really good.

40
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,100
I think Sister Li Meng is great too!

41
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,879
Uncle, Auntie. I'm off.

42
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,520
- Brother! 
 - Take care.

43
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:37,199
Not even food can stop your mouth.

44
00:03:37,199 --> 00:03:38,799
Sit down.

45
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:41,280
Seriously. Watch what you say.

46
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:43,080
Why do you keep saying stuff that hurts your cousin?

47
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:46,219
That's right. You need to learn to grasp the mood.

48
00:03:46,219 --> 00:03:48,680
Eat the fritter you like. I bought it just for you.

49
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:50,718
Eat your food.

50
00:03:56,871 --> 00:03:58,571
 Yan! 

51
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,140
 Yan. 

52
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:01,520
Auntie.

53
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:03,520
Here. You didn't have any soy milk just now.

54
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,879
Take this.

55
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:08,319
It's okay. You didn't have to come running with it.

56
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:12,099
I hope you didn't take what Zhai Miao just said to heart.

57
00:04:12,099 --> 00:04:13,699
It's okay.

58
00:04:14,788 --> 00:04:16,623
But with some things,

59
00:04:16,623 --> 00:04:18,959
I think it's better to accept reality and move on.

60
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:20,199
Be more open-minded.

61
00:04:20,199 --> 00:04:23,399
After all, there's too much bad blood between our families.

62
00:04:23,399 --> 00:04:25,839
But our family history is unrelated to her.

63
00:04:25,839 --> 00:04:27,759
It relates to you, though.

64
00:04:27,759 --> 00:04:29,480
Did you forget all the things you went through?

65
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:33,099
You can't expect us to pretend it never happened.

66
00:04:33,099 --> 00:04:35,960
Don't worry. I'll handle it.

67
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:42,060
You aren't determined to reconcile with her, are you?

68
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,800
A lot of things aren't always under our control.

69
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:52,600
It's complicated, for her and for me.

70
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:55,600
I'll just go with the flow.

71
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,820
All right, hurry back.

72
00:04:58,820 --> 00:05:00,360
Don't be too harsh on yourself.

73
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:02,000
Remember to drink the soy milk!

74
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,660
- I will. 
 - It has a short shelf life.

75
00:05:34,399 --> 00:05:36,879
Captain Song, are you heading to the station?

76
00:05:36,879 --> 00:05:38,579
Get in.

77
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:49,240
I seem to remember you don't live around here. Are you passing by?

78
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:54,099
I heard there's a nice cake shop in the area, so I came to buy some.

79
00:05:54,099 --> 00:05:56,240
Later, I'd take some to the station.

80
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,499
It's okay. I don't really like sweet stuff.

81
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:04,039
It's not only for you. It's for the whole team.

82
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,760
Okay.

83
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:04,000
Do you still like her?

84
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,560
What a surprise.

85
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:11,720
You're actually the masochistic type.

86
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:16,520
I mean, you're too low for her taste. Why bother?

87
00:07:19,279 --> 00:07:24,279
Who gave her the right to belittle you and be dismissive of a good person like you?

88
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:26,399
You should show her.

89
00:07:26,399 --> 00:07:28,279
There are many equally great ladies who like you.

90
00:07:28,279 --> 00:07:29,480
Li Meng.

91
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,279
If you keep going,

92
00:07:31,279 --> 00:07:33,401
you're treading a thin line.

93
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:39,060
You really annoy me.

94
00:07:39,060 --> 00:07:43,763
I mean, you have good character, good looks and everything. But?

95
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:45,959
You have to hang yourself on one tree.

96
00:07:45,959 --> 00:07:48,260
That's enough. Stop.

97
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:56,960
I thank you for your concern.

98
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,940
Anyway,

99
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:03,319
my relationship with my ex-girlfriend, whether it's good or bad,

100
00:08:03,319 --> 00:08:06,460
isn't for others to meddle in.

101
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:08,160
Understood?

102
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:12,000
Fine, I'm sorry.

103
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,439
I know I shouldn't say these things.

104
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:15,939
It's rude.

105
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,524
I couldn't help myself.

106
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:23,500
I've told you before, right? You and I are impossible.

107
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:25,459
So what if you have?

108
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:28,380
Are you dictating what I should do?

109
00:08:29,042 --> 00:08:33,179
You ask why I do this to myself. Then why are you doing this?

110
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,599
It's easy for you to criticize others.

111
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,286
You like her, but you don't like me.

112
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:42,360
I can't do anything about it.

113
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,200
But can't you at least find someone who treats you better?

114
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,819
At least, let me feel convinced.

115
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:51,399
I'm still trying to convince myself.

116
00:08:51,399 --> 00:08:53,904
Who can give me a reasonable answer?

117
00:09:03,443 --> 00:09:07,405
   

118
00:09:08,558 --> 00:09:13,080
Auntie Jia, why can't I continue to stay here?

119
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,879
Because the hospital is a place for sick people.

120
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:18,140
Then I want to be sick a long time.

121
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:20,879
Don't be silly. You can't always be sick.

122
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:23,639
Later, a lady from the Women's Association will take you to the orphanage.

123
00:09:23,639 --> 00:09:25,720
There will be lots of other children there.

124
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:29,140
And the teachers will teach you to read and write.

125
00:09:29,140 --> 00:09:30,720
I don't have any money.

126
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:34,080
They're going to kick me out.

127
00:09:34,879 --> 00:09:36,559
You don't need money there.

128
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:39,320
Is that true, Auntie Qin Qin?

129
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,679
Yes, that's right.

130
00:09:40,679 --> 00:09:42,960
Then will you come play with me?

131
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,360
I will.

132
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,960
Pinky promise.

133
00:09:46,399 --> 00:09:51,599
♪ You make a pinky promise, you keep it all your life ♪

134
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:13,559
Doctor, my mom is having trouble breathing.

135
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:15,380
Come, hurry, sit down.

136
00:10:15,380 --> 00:10:18,785
- How long has this gone on? 
 - About 40 minutes.

137
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:21,080
I'll give you a prescription for oxygen therapy first.

138
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,679
Oxygen therapy doesn't work.

139
00:10:22,679 --> 00:10:25,240
It actually exacerbates the condition.

140
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:27,193
- Does she have any underlying illnesses? 
 - No.

141
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:29,360
She's been to your hospital many times.

142
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,939
She was given a clean bill of health.

143
00:10:31,939 --> 00:10:33,860
Is this the usual symptom?

144
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:36,919
Yes. Every time, she says she can't breathe,

145
00:10:36,919 --> 00:10:38,080
that it's hard to breathe.

146
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:41,656
But when we come to the hospital, we can't find anything wrong with her.

147
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,960
Don't panic.

148
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,920
Turn around.

149
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,059
Breathe in.

150
00:10:56,059 --> 00:10:57,459
Breathe out.

151
00:11:01,328 --> 00:11:02,919
Has she done a lung CT scan before?

152
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:04,419
Yes.

153
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:11,000
From this scan, everything looks fine.

154
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,360
I also didn't find anything unusual when I listened to her lungs.

155
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:20,360
I think your mother could have psychological hysteria.

156
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:24,399
That means, physically, she's okay, but she believes otherwise.

157
00:11:24,399 --> 00:11:26,759
When you keep giving yourself these psychological hints over a long period,

158
00:11:26,759 --> 00:11:28,279
the body starts to overreact.

159
00:11:28,279 --> 00:11:30,159
It's fine. It's nothing to worry about.

160
00:11:30,159 --> 00:11:32,399
Doctor, at least give her some medication.

161
00:11:32,399 --> 00:11:34,639
She doesn't need medication because she's not sick.

162
00:11:34,639 --> 00:11:37,960
Aside from the breathing difficulty, do you have any other symptoms?

163
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:40,299
Director.

164
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:45,889
This symptom of yours, does it happen often?

165
00:11:45,889 --> 00:11:48,240
- Yes. 
 - It comes and goes.

166
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,919
Get me a clean plastic bag.

167
00:11:49,919 --> 00:11:51,319
Okay.

168
00:11:52,879 --> 00:11:55,700
Relax. Let's try this.

169
00:11:56,559 --> 00:11:58,909
It could work.

170
00:11:58,909 --> 00:12:01,880
Now, now, relax. Hold this.

171
00:12:05,590 --> 00:12:09,559
I think your mother is suffering from hyperventilation.

172
00:12:09,559 --> 00:12:13,360
Due to the hyperventilation, her carbon dioxide level becomes low.

173
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:17,600
With the bag over her head, her carbon dioxide level can increase.

174
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,000
Monitor it for a bit.

175
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,500
Here.

176
00:12:34,919 --> 00:12:36,419
How do you feel now?

177
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,399
Much better.

178
00:12:39,399 --> 00:12:41,661
I can catch my breath now.

179
00:12:41,661 --> 00:12:43,159
It's not anything serious.

180
00:12:43,159 --> 00:12:46,480
But I suggest that you go and see a psychiatrist.

181
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:48,440
"A psychiatrist"?

182
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:51,120
- Okay? 
 - Okay. Thank you.

183
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,520
Careful.

184
00:12:54,799 --> 00:12:56,000
Take it easy.

185
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,440
Xu Qin.

186
00:12:57,440 --> 00:13:00,939
For a patient like her,

187
00:13:00,939 --> 00:13:05,399
my first diagnosis is that she's reached menopause.

188
00:13:05,399 --> 00:13:11,039
It's very likely that due to various circumstances in her life or family,

189
00:13:11,039 --> 00:13:14,779
she's feeling a lot of stress and emotional distress.

190
00:13:14,779 --> 00:13:17,313
Do you know what you did wrong?

191
00:13:17,313 --> 00:13:21,419
As doctors, we're not only treating the illness.

192
00:13:21,419 --> 00:13:23,639
We must also know to read a person.

193
00:13:54,549 --> 00:13:56,559
Instructor, Instructor. What's the situation?

194
00:13:56,559 --> 00:13:58,879
Eight hikers went up Phoenix Mountain and got trapped.

195
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:01,279
- How long has it been? 
 - They went in yesterday at noon.

196
00:14:01,279 --> 00:14:02,879
The alert was sent this morning.

197
00:14:02,879 --> 00:14:06,039
 Their GPS device isn't working. They only have a contour map. 

198
00:14:06,039 --> 00:14:07,600
 They entered at the back of the mountain. 

199
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,039
They snuck in without getting an official permit.

200
00:14:10,039 --> 00:14:12,320
The weather is bad. It rained the whole night on the mountain.

201
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:15,279
One of the victims' fathers called the local rescue team for help.

202
00:14:15,279 --> 00:14:17,200
 In the end, the rescue team also got trapped. 

203
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:18,720
Do we have the exact location?

204
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,840
 Only a rough description. 

205
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,540
Okay, roger that.

206
00:14:47,799 --> 00:14:49,600
When will that be?

207
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,400
How much longer?

208
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,679
You guys are finally here.

209
00:14:55,679 --> 00:14:58,000
We just got here ourselves. The family members are very anxious.

210
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,159
They want us to head up the mountain right away.

211
00:15:00,159 --> 00:15:01,480
First, we have to be briefed.

212
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,240
We need to know where the victims are, at least.

213
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,600
I know that, but look...

214
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:08,240
We shouldn't rush in before getting to know the area.

215
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:11,320
Mr. Firefighter, our children have been out of reach for a day already.

216
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:13,904
Lives are at stake. Why aren't you guys going to save them yet?

217
00:15:13,904 --> 00:15:15,200
How about this?

218
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,620
I'll pay. Is ¥100,000  (~$14,000)  enough?

219
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:19,240
No? I can add ¥50,000 more.

220
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,799
Or you name a price.

221
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:23,279
I'm willing to pay however much, so long as you rescue them right now.

222
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:24,960
This has nothing to do with money.

223
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,639
This isn't... this isn't about money!

224
00:15:27,639 --> 00:15:29,440
Without first understanding the surrounding area,

225
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,840
we'll be acting irresponsibly toward the trapped.

226
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,440
Mr. Firefighter, my son is a senior-year student.

227
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:36,159
They all go to famous universities.

228
00:15:36,159 --> 00:15:37,689
They're all future talents.

229
00:15:37,689 --> 00:15:39,169
My sister is a freshman!

230
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:42,960
Your kids are children.

231
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:45,240
Us firefighters are also someone else's children.

232
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:48,440
No matter whose child, they shouldn't be put at risk randomly.

233
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:51,559
Everyone, which one of you knows the back mountain terrain?

234
00:15:51,559 --> 00:15:52,840
Yes, me.

235
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:55,679
I'm a local resident. I know this area.

236
00:15:55,679 --> 00:15:56,960
I'm going to set up the drone.

237
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:59,200
Actually, after listening to them talking,

238
00:15:59,200 --> 00:16:01,559
my guess is that those kids aren't on the back mountain.

239
00:16:01,559 --> 00:16:04,960
The terrain there is complicated. They probably found a stream and followed it.

240
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,399
They could have reached the main mountain.

241
00:16:06,399 --> 00:16:07,519
- "Main mountain"? 
 - Yes.

242
00:16:07,519 --> 00:16:09,859
- There's a boulder on the main mountain, too? 
 - Yes.

243
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,799
Where's the main mountain?

244
00:16:19,799 --> 00:16:21,600
Right here. Take a look. At this spot.

245
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,399
Tell me if I marked it correctly.

246
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,120
- Is it here? 
 - Yes. There's also a boulder here.

247
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,759
The boulder is named Ji Ming Rock.

248
00:16:26,759 --> 00:16:28,679
We often went there to pick medicinal herbs.

249
00:16:28,679 --> 00:16:30,960
But the herbs became scarce, so we stopped going.

250
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,759
There are lots of snakes too. Not many go there now.

251
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:35,399
The terrain is even trickier there.

252
00:16:35,399 --> 00:16:37,079
It'd be a problem if they were there.

253
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,040
Got it.

254
00:16:46,600 --> 00:16:48,583
Everyone, please calm down.

255
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:50,000
- Captain. 
 - Gather around.

256
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,680
I'll brief you on the situation.

257
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:54,600
Here's the thing.

258
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:58,200
Look here. There are two similar boulders in this area.

259
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:00,039
The description given by the hikers previously could be wrong.

260
00:17:00,039 --> 00:17:03,619
That led the civilian rescue team to Ying Zui Rock on the back mountain.

261
00:17:03,619 --> 00:17:07,394
According to the local resident, there's a Ji Ming Rock on the main mountain.

