00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:07,200
Captain?

560
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:08,900
Captain!

561
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:12,079
- Captain! 
 - Captain!

562
00:34:12,079 --> 00:34:13,779
Junping!

563
00:34:31,599 --> 00:34:32,719
Ambulance! Quickly!

564
00:34:32,719 --> 00:34:34,705
Get him to the hospital.

565
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:42,360
Old Jiang.

566
00:34:42,360 --> 00:34:44,320
Here you go.

567
00:34:44,320 --> 00:34:45,820
Cover yourself up.

568
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,979
Here, quick. Drink some water.

569
00:34:51,979 --> 00:34:53,559
- Instructor Jiang. 
 - Jiang Yi.

570
00:34:53,559 --> 00:34:55,199
Give me a minute.

571
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:56,899
Eat something.

572
00:35:02,719 --> 00:35:04,419
Eat this.

573
00:35:05,236 --> 00:35:06,800
I'm fine.

574
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:10,320
Save the food for the hikers and their families.

575
00:35:10,320 --> 00:35:13,839
What hikers and families? They're long gone.

576
00:35:15,898 --> 00:35:17,720
They already left?

577
00:35:19,159 --> 00:35:20,960
They used the excuse of taking the hikers to the hospital.

578
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:24,500
It's probably so they could avoid the press and possible punishment.

579
00:35:28,119 --> 00:35:30,579
Who would punish them?

580
00:36:06,366 --> 00:36:07,840
You're not sleeping?

581
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:09,240
Aren't you tired?

582
00:36:11,119 --> 00:36:12,519
I'm fine.

583
00:36:13,432 --> 00:36:15,132
Do you...

584
00:36:16,199 --> 00:36:18,339
come across these incidents often?

585
00:36:19,119 --> 00:36:23,459
If we're looking at the frequency, it's been decreasing year by year

586
00:36:23,459 --> 00:36:25,980
because the environment is improving.

587
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:31,019
It really sucks having to deal with these things.

588
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:36,528
Are you already complaining over such a small matter?

589
00:36:36,528 --> 00:36:39,280
Objectively, such difficulties aren't that bad.

590
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:41,332
It's the mental pressure...

591
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:44,101
that bothers me.

592
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:47,610
I told you a long time ago.

593
00:36:47,610 --> 00:36:49,507
You're too idealistic.

594
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:52,734
You've been under a glass cover too long. 
  (T/N: protected) 

595
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:56,340
Are you attacking me again?

596
00:36:56,340 --> 00:36:57,740
I'm not.

597
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:03,120
Your performance today was quite good.

598
00:37:05,246 --> 00:37:08,099
Since we're on the topic, be frank with me.

599
00:37:08,099 --> 00:37:11,300
Do you really think I'm idealistic?

600
00:37:11,300 --> 00:37:14,132
Did you think...

601
00:37:14,132 --> 00:37:18,805
I chose this career because I wanted glory?

602
00:37:18,805 --> 00:37:21,239
Or perhaps a short-lived passion?

603
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:23,380
When the passion is gone,

604
00:37:23,380 --> 00:37:25,960
so is the halo,

605
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:28,580
and then my ideals are shattered?

606
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:33,619
Your critique is really accurate.

607
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:38,160
Let me tell you the truth.

608
00:37:40,079 --> 00:37:42,559
I thought long and hard before I made the decision.

609
00:37:42,559 --> 00:37:46,659
Like you said, I did have a lot of options.

610
00:37:46,659 --> 00:37:50,308
But that doesn't mean my choice...

611
00:37:51,079 --> 00:37:54,400
isn't as serious or worthy as yours.

612
00:37:54,400 --> 00:37:59,059
I never thought about glory or wanting to be a hero.

613
00:38:00,519 --> 00:38:03,059
I just purely like this job.

614
00:38:04,360 --> 00:38:06,609
I wish to contribute to it.

615
00:38:06,609 --> 00:38:08,417
You could even say

616
00:38:09,679 --> 00:38:11,899
I wish to become better day by day.

617
00:38:15,079 --> 00:38:16,760
You know something?

618
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:22,059
Every time I'm in the shower, and the water splashes on my head,

619
00:38:22,599 --> 00:38:24,702
three things pop into my mind.

620
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:29,407
I hope to integrate into the team quickly.

621
00:38:31,079 --> 00:38:33,677
I hope to become stronger.

622
00:38:34,599 --> 00:38:36,747
And I hope I can do more

623
00:38:38,239 --> 00:38:40,417
for the fire station.

624
00:38:49,880 --> 00:38:52,000
